xyz.swatt.data_mapping_validator

Class DateTimeMappingValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.swatt.data_mapping_validator.AbstractDataMapping<DateTimeMappingValidator.LocalDateTimeTuple>
      • xyz.swatt.data_mapping_validator.DateTimeMappingValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataMappingValidator<DateTimeMappingValidator.LocalDateTimeTuple> 

    @LogMethods
public class DateTimeMappingValidator
extends AbstractDataMapping<DateTimeMappingValidator.LocalDateTimeTuple>

    Use this class to validate that 2 different Temporals representing Date and/or Time are equal.

    Note: All Temporals are converted to DateTimeMappingValidator.LocalDateTimeTuples, before comparison.

    Warning: Be careful when comparing Date/Times both with and without Time Zones. Date/Times without Time Zones will be treated as having come from the Local (System Default) Time Zone.

     

    This DataMappingValidator has been tested with:

    • LocalDateTime
    • LocalDate
    • LocalTime
    • Date
    • Date
    • Timestamp
    • Instant
    • ZonedDateTime
    • OffsetDateTime
    • OffsetTime
    Author:
    Brandon Dudek (BrandonDudek)
